EOF

# Install Mono and compile
sudo apt install mono-devel -y
mcs VulnerableApp.cs -out:VulnerableApp.exe
Task 2: Analyze Native Binaries with Ghidra
Step 2.1: Create Ghidra Project
# Launch Ghidra
cd ~/lab11-binary-analysis
./ghidra/ghidraRun &
In Ghidra GUI:

File → New Project → Non-Shared Project
Set directory: ~/lab11-binary-analysis/ghidra_projects
Name: BinaryAnalysis
Click Finish
Step 2.2: Import and Analyze Binary
Click Import File (dragon icon)
Select vulnerable_app binary
Accept default settings → OK
Double-click imported file to open CodeBrowser
When prompted, click Yes to analyze
In Analysis Options:
Check "Decompiler Parameter ID"
Check "Function Start Search"
Click Analyze
Step 2.3: Examine Decompiled Code
Navigate the analysis:

Symbol Tree (left panel) → Functions → main
View decompiled C code in Decompiler window (right)
Locate buffer_overflow_vuln function
Identify the strcpy call without bounds checking
Find format_string_vuln with unsafe printf
Note system() call with user input
