Troubleshooting Tips
Ghidra Won't Start
Verify Java 17 is installed: java -version
Check Ghidra permissions: chmod +x ghidra/ghidraRun
Review logs: ~/lab11-binary-analysis/ghidra/ghidra.log
dotPeek Installation Issues
Ensure Wine is properly configured: winecfg
Try 32-bit version if 64-bit fails
Check Wine logs: ~/.wine/drive_c/users/*/Temp/
Headless Analysis Fails
Verify binary is executable: file vulnerable_app
Check project path permissions
Increase timeout in subprocess.run()
Conclusion
This lab introduced binary reverse engineering using Ghidra and dotPeek. You learned to:

Decompile native and .NET binaries
Identify security vulnerabilities through static analysis
Automate analysis workflows with Python
Generate professional security reports
These skills are essential for security auditing, malware analysis, and vulnerability research. Practice analyzing different binaries to strengthen your reverse engineering capabilities.

